External knowledge: 
BMI (Body Mass Index) is a measure of body fat based on height and weight; 
A higher BMI can indicate a higher risk of health issues; 
Dependent age can affect a family's overall health and well-being; 
Claim history and claim amount can be indicators of health issues and medical expenses; 
Hypertension is a medical condition that can increase the risk of heart disease, stroke, and other health problems; 
The comprehensive health risk score is a simple sum of the above factors, with some normalization to make the values comparable.
